# =============================================================================
# Line Calls — .gitignore
#
# Goal: commit the things that took human effort and are small (code, docs,
# hand-labeled CSVs, calibration), and keep out anything big or reproducible
# (videos, extracted frames, model weights, packaged zips, the vendored repo).
# =============================================================================

# --- Python environment & caches ---
.venv/
**/.venv/
__pycache__/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# --- Video clips (large; store these outside git, e.g. a synced drive) ---
*.mp4
*.mov
*.avi
*.mkv
*.m4v

# --- Extracted frames (regenerated from video by label_ball.py on demand) ---
*_frames/

# --- Packaged training sets & backups (rebuilt by build_finetune_zip.py) ---
finetune_data*.zip
*.zip.bak
*.bak

# --- Model checkpoints (large; downloaded or produced separately) ---
*.pt
*.pth
*.onnx

# --- Vendored upstream repo: a clone of github.com/qaz812345/TrackNetV3 ---
# It's reproducible with `git clone`, so it stays out of your repo.
# NOTE: if you've customized any file inside it (e.g. finetune.py), copy that
# file OUT to a tracked location so this rule doesn't lose your edits.
TrackNetV3/

# --- Stray / scratch files ---
ziJF24ID

# =============================================================================
# Deliberately KEPT (do not ignore): these are small and worth versioning
#   *.py, *.ipynb, *.md            -> code, notebooks, docs
#   labeled_data/**/*.csv          -> your hand-labeled ground-truth (the crown jewels)
#   phase1/court_calibration.json  -> calibration
#   requirements.txt               -> dependencies
# =============================================================================
